**3. FirestoreArticleDataSourceImpl**:

```dart
@override
Future<PaginatedArticlesResult> getUserArticlesPage({
  required int limit,
  DocumentSnapshot? startAfter,
}) async {
  Query query = _firestore
      .collection('articles')
      .where('isUserArticle', isEqualTo: true)
      .orderBy('createdAt', descending: true)
      .limit(limit);

  if (startAfter != null) {
    query = query.startAfterDocument(startAfter);
  }

  final querySnapshot = await query.get();
  final articles = querySnapshot.docs
      .map((doc) => ArticleModel.fromFirestore(doc))
      .toList();

  final hasMore = querySnapshot.docs.length == limit;
  final lastDoc = querySnapshot.docs.isNotEmpty ? querySnapshot.docs.last : null;

  return PaginatedArticlesResult(
    articles: articles,
    lastDocument: lastDoc,
    hasMore: hasMore,
  );
}
```

The default page size should be 20 (configurable via a constant). The `hasMore` flag is determined by whether the returned count equals the limit (if fewer are returned, there are no more pages).

